messages.content:
Yet another video call where nods are read as agreements, nods shield thoughts away to stay safe under watchful web eyes. Real laughs over zoom are rare finds like the golden nuggets they turn out to be once seen. True intimacy? Physical presence still reigns supreme. Here's wishing every face an embrace, every glance a chance to laugh face to face again! 🥃'}}
{
Victor Clark
Too much typing and too little hugging—that’s the state of social interaction today. Digital hi turned into so minimal human exchange it’s absurd. Bringing drinks again won’t fix fingers lost virtual or friendships dried through tiny avatars. Long to reclaim those spontaneous chats where faces matched the words heard, not just liked. Needing something tangible, right now more than ever. 👿☕ #MissHugsOverMessages #BringOnTrueCon #BackToFace
